ek.at/en/event/93/takashi-ohno-no-more-fukushimas/index.html|title=Events|date=7 August 2014|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marcello-farabegoli.net/no-more-fukushimas.html|title=No more Fukushimas|website=www.marcello-farabegoli.net|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[http://derstandard.at/2000008436072/Reisbaellchen-aus-Fukushima Article by Anne Katrin Fe\u00dfler in] [[Der Standard]] (Austrian newspaper), November 20, 2014</ref><ref>[https://diepresse.com/home/kultur/kunst/4602199/Sieben-Tage-Visionen-fuer-den-Kunststandort-Wien Article by Sabine B. Vogel in] [[Die Presse]] (Austrian newspaper), November 23, 2014</ref><ref>[http://www.wienerzeitung.at/nachrichten/welt/weltpolitik/708432_Japan-liebaeugelt-wieder-mit-Atomkraft.html Article in] [[Wiener Zeitung]] (Austrian newspaper), November 18, 2014</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artribune.com/arti-visive/arte-contemporanea/2014/12/fukushima-mon-amour-la-mostra-dellanno-a-vienna/|title=Fukushima mon amour! La mostra dell\u2019anno a Vienna? - Artribune|first=Franco|last=Veremondi|date=6 December 2014|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[http://www.altoadige.it/cultura-e-spettacoli/la-mostra-viennese-di-farabegoli-1.173780 Article in] [[Alto Adige (newspaper)|Alto Adige]] (Italian newspaper), December 9, 2014</ref>\n* 2014,  ''Salotto.Vienna'' (Viennese Art Salon) at ex Pescheria \u2013 Salone degli Incanti in [[Trieste]] (IT): Presented by [[Museum of Applied Arts, Vienna|MAK \u2013 Austrian Museum of Applied Arts / Contemporary Art]]; curated and produced by J\u00fcrgen F. Weish\u00e4upl; co-curated by Giovanni Damiani, Marcello Farabegoli and Giulio Polita; Viennese institutions represented: [[21er Haus]] \u2013 [[\u00d6sterreichische Galerie Belvedere]], Akademie des \u00d6sterreichischen Films, [[Haus der Musik]], [[ImPulsTanz Vienna International Dance Festival|ImPulsTanz]], [[Kunsthalle Wien]], [[KunstHausWien]] \u2013 Museum Hundertwasse