{"title_page": "SmileML", "text_new": "{{db-spam|help=off}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = SmileML, Inc.\n| logo                = SmileML_Logo.png\n| type                = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry            = Software\n| founded             = {{Start date and age|2017|12|17}}\n| founder             = {{Unbulleted list|Ethan Petersen|}}\n| hq_location_city    = [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n| hq_location_country = [[United States]]\n| products            = {{URL|salespot.io|SaleSpot}}\n| website             = {{URL|smile-ml.com}}\n}}\nSmileML, Inc., commonly known as smileML, is a software development company specializing in [[Edge computing|edge-based]] [[emotion recognition]] and [[machine learning]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smile-ml.com/|title=smileML {{!}} Making Emotion Recognition an Exact Science|website=www.smile-ml.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> SmileML has developed camera-agnostic technology that analyzes facial expressions and gait to interpret the emotional state of an individual.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smile-ml.com/technology|title=smileML {{!}} Technology|website=www.smile-ml.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Commercially, SmileML's technology is being used to analyze sentiment and body language during sales video calls to help sales teams transitioning to remote work improve customer engagement and receptiveness. \n\n== History ==\nSmileML was inspired by the founders' experience developing [[:simple:IOS|iOS apps]]. While conducting [[user research]] before launching an app, they began using emotion recognition during user research interviews to get a better understanding of how people feel about consumer products and websites.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edu.google.com/why-google/case-studies/smileml/|title=Case Studies: SmileML|last=|first=|date=|website=Google for Education|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-03|dead-url=}}</ref> In 2019, SmileML completed with [http://techstars.blog/content/accelerators/air-force-accelerator-powered-techstars-proudly-announces-class-2019/ Techstars Air Force Accelerator] where it began developing its sales analytics product, [https://www.salespot.io/ SaleSpot].\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External Links ==\n\n* [https://www.smile-ml.com/ Official Website]\n", "text_old": "{{db-spam|help=off}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = SmileML, Inc.\n| logo                = SmileML_Logo.png\n| type                = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry            = Software\n| founded             = {{Start date and age|2017|12|17}}\n| founder             = {{Unbulleted list|Ethan Petersen|}}\n| hq_location_city    = [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n| hq_location_country = [[United States]]\n| products            = {{URL|salespot.io|SaleSpot}}\n| website             = {{URL|smile-ml.com}}\n}}\nSmileML, Inc., commonly known as smileML, is a software development company specializing in [[Edge computing|edge-based]] [[emotion recognition]] and [[machine learning]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smile-ml.com/|title=smileML {{!}} Making Emotion Recognition an Exact Science|website=www.smile-ml.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> SmileML has developed camera-agnostic technology that analyzes facial expressions and gait to interpret the emotional state of an individual.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smile-ml.com/technology|title=smileML {{!}} Technology|website=www.smile-ml.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Commercially, SmileML's technology is being used to analyze sentiment and body language during sales video calls to help sales teams in their transition to remote work improve customer engagement and receptiveness. \n\n== History ==\nSmileML was inspired by the founders' experience developing [[:simple:IOS|iOS apps]]. While conducting [[user research]] before launching an app, they began using emotion recognition during user research interviews to get a better understanding of how people feel about consumer products and websites.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edu.google.com/why-google/case-studies/smileml/|title=Case Studies: SmileML|last=|first=|date=|website=Google for Education|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-03|dead-url=}}</ref> In 2019, SmileML completed with [http://techstars.blog/content/accelerators/air-force-accelerator-powered-techstars-proudly-announces-class-2019/ Techstars Air Force Accelerator] where it began developing its sales analytics product, [https://www.salespot.io/ SaleSpot].\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External Links ==\n\n* [https://www.smile-ml.com/ Official Website]\n", "name_user": "Shanxanderson", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor grammar changes", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SmileML"}
